      • populateGraph

        public java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.String,java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String>> populateGraph()
        This method creates a Hashtable> from an ArrayList< String >. It goes through every word in the ArrayList< String> , creating another ArrayList< String > that contains all the words that have a one character difference from it. After creating the ArrayList< String> , the word and ArrayList< String > are placed in the Hashtable as a node key and value respectively.
        Returns:
        - Hashtable< String, ArrayList< String > >
